field.value:
When using async actions in Mono, the context is incorrectly assigned somewhere along the line and the SessionWebModule or custom session handling methods cannot successfully release the original Activerecord session.  To fix this, the context must be assigned in the End portion of the async action with

{code lang=csharp}
HttpContext.Current = HttpContext;
{code}

I'm not sure exactly where this can be placed to work correctly with Mono, perhaps in BaseAsyncHttpHandler's EndProcessRequest finally block as:

{code lang=csharp}
HttpContext.Current = httpContext;
{code}
